Database Rules
Schema Immutability

Never modify schema.sql directly after the first migration
All schema changes go in numbered migration files: migrations/001_add_column.sql, migrations/002_create_index.sql
migrate.php tracks applied migrations in a _migrations table
Production migrations must be reversible — include a -- DOWN section in each migration file

Query Patterns
Always Filter Soft Deletes
sql-- CORRECT
SELECT * FROM tasks WHERE project_id = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
-- WRONG — never omit this
SELECT * FROM tasks WHERE project_id = ?
Fractional Display Order Queries
sql-- Get tasks for Kanban column ordered correctly
SELECT * FROM tasks
WHERE status = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
ORDER BY display_order ASC, created_at ASC
Joining for Relations
sql-- Always LEFT JOIN — don't INNER JOIN relations that may be NULL
SELECT t.*, p.title AS project_title, p.color AS project_color
FROM tasks t
LEFT JOIN projects p ON t.project_id = p.id AND p.deleted_at IS NULL
WHERE t.id = ? AND t.deleted_at IS NULL
Pagination
sqlSELECT * FROM tasks WHERE deleted_at IS NULL
ORDER BY created_at DESC
LIMIT ? OFFSET ?
-- Always pair with a COUNT(*) query for total
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM tasks WHERE deleted_at IS NULL
Index Rules

Every foreign key column must have an index
Every column used in WHERE filters must have an index
Compound index for Kanban: (status, display_order)
Compound index for diary timeline: (logged_at DESC)
Never index columns that are only in SELECT — only WHERE/ORDER BY/JOIN columns

SQLite-Specific Gotchas

AUTOINCREMENT is slower than just INTEGER PRIMARY KEY — use the latter unless you need guaranteed non-reuse of IDs (we do not)
WAL mode must be set on every new connection — it's not persisted in the file header reliably
unixepoch() is the correct SQLite function for current Unix timestamp (not strftime('%s','now'))
Foreign key enforcement is OFF by default — always PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON
JSON columns are TEXT — SQLite has no native JSON type; validate structure in PHP before writing
Boolean columns: INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0 CHECK(col IN (0,1)) — never BOOLEAN type

Daily Snapshot Builder
SnapshotService::buildForDate(string $date) must:

Count tasks where due_date falls within the day and deleted_at IS NULL → tasks_planned
Count tasks where completed_at falls within the day → tasks_completed
Count tasks where created_at falls within the day → tasks_added
Count diary logs for the day → log_count
AVG mood/energy from diary logs for the day
UPSERT into daily_snapshots (INSERT OR REPLACE)
Run automatically at midnight via a cron job hitting POST /api/snapshots/build
